Coominglah (southwest of Gladstone) – bushfire as at 4pm Sun 21 Feb     Queensland Fire and Emergency Services (QFES) crews are currently on scene at a bushfire burning south of the Burnett Highway along Foleys Gully Road, Coominglah. The fire is posing no threat to property at this time. Firefighters are working to contain the blaze. Motorists travelling on the Burnett Highway may be affected by smoke and should drive with caution. Nearby residents are asked to close windows and doors and if suffering from a respiratory condition, keep medications close by. If residents are concerned their property is under threat they are advised to call Triple Zero (000) immediately.
